Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[A necropsy could find a number of different things. Heavy metals or an insecticide/herbicide screen could rule in or rule out the speculations above.

There have been cases of domoic acid poisoning turtles but there are no reports of domoic acid in the region mentioned.

Red tide has been known to affect turtles, but again, there seems to be no red tide in this area.

Parasites of the brain are another ailment of turtles, but it would seem unusual to have this many affected in a short period of time and a similar location.

We look forward to learning what is happening to these turtles.

A photo of Kemp's ridley turtle may be found at http://www.arkive.org/kemps-ridley-turtle/lepidochelys-kempii/

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Costa Rica may be found at http://healthmap.org/r/4_y* . - Mod.TG]
